               <head>Three works on tradition</head>
               <msContents class="http://id.loc.gov/authorities/subjects/sh91004954 http://id.loc.gov/authorities/subjects/sh85058192">
                  <msItem n="a">
                     <locus from="4v" to="16v">ff. 4v-16v</locus>
                     <author key="person_f8317">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Muḥammad Fayz̤ Vāsiṭī Bilgrāmī </persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">مهمد فیض الواسطی بلگرامی</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_23110">Tarjumah-ʼi Shamāʾil al-Nabī </title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_23110">ترجمهٔ شمایل نبی</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="fa">بسم الله…حمدی که مسبّحان صوامع جوامع معرفت از
                                ادای کنه حمدیت بعجز معترف … </incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="fa">و عمر وی هفتاد و چهارساله بود رح. الحمد الله علی
                                کل حال تحقیق اشمإ الرجال الشمایل مصنف مهمد فیض الواسطی
                                بالکرامی</explicit>
                     <note>
                        <p>The introductory portion of a Persian translation of <persName key="viaf_113733357" xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc">al-Tirmidhī</persName>’s <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" xml:id="work_675">Shamāʾil
                                        al-Nabī</title>, a collection of traditions concerning the
                                    person and character of the Prophet. Translated by Muḥammad
                                    Fayz̤ ibn Muḥammad Ṣādiq Ṣadr-i Jahān Ḥātim Badr al-Dīn
                                    al-Ḥusaynī al-Bilgrāmī al-Vāsiṭī al-Muḥammadī and completed in
                                    1112 (1700-1701). 
                        </p>
                     </note>
                     <note>Preceded (f. 1) by an index, headed <title>Fihrist-i Barzakh
                                </title>and the first leaf (f. 2) of what is possibly a Persian
                                translation of <persName xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_90051632">al-Suyūtī</persName>’s
                                    <title>Kitāb al-Barzakh</title>. Further table on f. 3r (ff.
                                3v-4r are blank). 
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="b" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_602-item2">
                     <locus from="17r" to="19r">ff. 17r-19r</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Arabic definitions of different kinds of traditions. </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="ar">Arabic</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="c" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_602-item3">
                     <locus from="21v" to="29v">ff. 21v-29v</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Chapters (faṣl) 2-4 and the heading of chapter 5 from an
                                    unidentified Arabic work on Ḥadith. </p>
                        <p>Preceded on f. 20v by a further index. </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="ar">Arabic</textLang>
                  </msItem>
